{"id": 38, "ts": 1778843097.9338765, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_2", "message": "I have reviewed all the explicit attributes we have for each candidate.\n**Candidate\u202fB** is the only person with clear, positive evidence for the two non\u2011negotiable criteria of a long\u2011distance pilot: *100\u202f% reliability* and *calmness in a crisis*. He also has solid technical skills (weather assessment, computer proficiency). The only documented drawbacks are interpersonal \u2013 he is described as uncooperative, grumpy, and makes nasty remarks toward colleagues. These are serious teamwork concerns, but they are the sole negatives for B.\n**Candidate\u202fA** shows strong technical and leadership abilities (anticipates danger, sees complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership). However, we have **no explicit evidence** that he can stay calm under pressure or that he is reliably punctual/procedural. The gaps in calmness and reliability are critical for international, high\u2011responsibility flights. His noted weaknesses (unorganized, not receptive to criticism, show\u2011off, resistant to new ideas) are also concerns but do not compensate for the missing safety\u2011critical evidence.\n**Candidate\u202fC** handles stress well, but we lack any reliability data and he has clear communication and attitude problems (egocentric, poor willingness to develop).\n**Candidate\u202fD** solves problems and concentrates well, yet we have no evidence of calmness under pressure or teamwork, and he is described as moody, hot\u2011tempered, a know\u2011it\u2011all, and a loner.\nGiven that reliability and calmness under pressure are essential and are **explicitly confirmed only for Candidate\u202fB**, while his teamwork issues, though serious, are the only negatives, I conclude that Candidate\u202fB best satisfies the core safety and performance requirements for a long\u2011distance pilot.\n**Vote:** Candidate B\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}"}
